wdi-FP.CPI.TOTL.ZG.def: Inflation as measured by the consumer price index reflects the annual percentage change in the cost to the average consumer of acquiring a basket of goods and services that may be fixed or changed at specified intervals, such as yearly. The Laspeyres formula is generally used.
wdi-FP.CPI.TOTL.ZG.name: Inflation
wdi-FP.CPI.TOTL.ZG.source: International Monetary Fund, International Financial Statistics and data files.
